    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-02-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="785"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received March 12.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 196.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am informed that the naturalized citizens of
                    the United States who have been so long detained at Alexandretta<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d785fn2">Mrs. Toprahanian was furnished in the summer of 1894 with a
                        United States passport, and by order of the Porte with a teskeré, or
                        traveling passport, to come from the interior of Asia Minor and embark with
                        her two children for the United States to join her husband, a resident of
                        New York. She was stopped at Alexandretta and detained there for more than
                        two months on the ground that she was a Turkish subject.</note> have been
                    ordered to depart from the Ottoman Empire.</p>
                <p>The man imprisoned at Yozgad,<note n="1" xml:id="d785fn1">Aivazian.</note> who
                    has been referred to in former dispatches, will, I have reason to believe, soon
                    be expelled also.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
